An unoriented graph with n nodes and m arcs is divided into 2 groups S and T, in a way such that the number of arcs with one end in S and the other in T is the maximum possible. We do not require an optimal solution, just a very close one to it, while maintaining a reasonable temporal complexity.

Input:
An undirected graph with n nodes and m edges.

Output:
The two sets S and T.

